dbStoredQuestions.questionText: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a horizontal or vertical number line.

standards.description: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a horizontal or vertical number line.
standards.subject: Mathematics

rigor.justification: The items primarily require procedural computation (prime factorization, adding/subtracting/multiplying/dividing integers, plotting/comparing integers on a number line, and evaluating expressions using order of operations). These are routine procedures and simple applications of rules rather than multi-step problem solving or deep reasoning, so Depth of Knowledge is centered at DOK 1 (recall/perform) and low DOK 2 (basic application).
